<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-12-01T23:55:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-12-31T23:56:00-05:00" n="209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                                    <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-chapter-head">[Bavaria]</head>
                                    <opener>
                                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1873-12-01T23:59:59-04:56" notBefore="1873-01-01T00:00:00-04:56">undated</date>.]</dateline>
                                    </opener>
                                    <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">naturalization of
                                            aliens</hi>.</p>
                                    <p>Naturalization is acquired— <list>
                                            <label>1.</label>
                                            <item>By the marriage of a foreign woman with a
                                                  Bavarian;<note n="2" xml:id="d209fn2">Fœlix, vol.
                                                  i, p. 99.</note></item>
                                            <label>2.</label>
                                            <item>By domicile, on affording proof of having been
                                                liberated from personal allegiance to a foreign
                                                  state;<note n="3" xml:id="d209fn3">Sir
                                                  <persName>R. Phillimore</persName>, vol. 1. p.
                                                  352.</note></item>
                                            <label>3.</label>
                                            <item>By royal decree, under the supervision of the
                                                council of state.</item>
                                        </list></p>
                                    <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">expatriation</hi>.</p>
                                    <p>By naturalization in a foreign country without having
                                        previously obtained authorization from the King;</p>
                                    <p>By emigration;</p>
                                    <p>By the marriage of a Bavarian woman with an alien.</p>
                                </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>